content.description: Starts with sloping dish in left hand and a side pull ledge in the right. Left foot in a low dish and right foot goes high above waist on a decent sloping ledge. Try not to use good crimp from "Bird Call" just to the right. No real holds higher up, only one last ditch effort ledge on the left side of the problem.
content.location: Boulder between "Bird Call" and "Juniper's Landing". Pull away the last 3 feet of the juniper bush and start right there.

content.description: Starts on a good sharp diagonal ledge for left hand, with a decent side pull for right hand. Right foot starts wide right on a little side ledge, smear with left foot. Not many other holds, top is a reach with a really sharp piece of quartz. Get around the quartz and there is a decent ledge get your fingers around to pull yourself up.
content.location: Just to the left of "Bird Call" and "Last Ditch Effort", standing on top of the main section of the Juniper bush.

content.description: Fun little crack you can do however you want. Good way to practice a couple hand placements for longer routes. Needs some cleaning.
content.location: Left of Juniper's Landing. Watch the bush, its a bit of a pain to get around.

content.description: The problem starts about half way along the little cliff. Nice little problem, no feet for the start, mostly small edges and some smearing.
content.location: Start at the 90 degree angle cut in the rock(see image), and go straight up using the most obvious holds. Top is slopey with few holds, but you're not that high up.

content.description: There are a few short but clean boulders on the climbers right side of the overlook. This cliff is climbed out, but if one is in the area these boulders are a fun set of slabs to do without pads.
